text: Nizhniye Karamaly () is a rural locality (a village) in Bakeyevsky Selsoviet, Sterlibashevsky District, Bashkortostan, Russia. The population was 29 as of 2010. There is 1 street. == Geography == It is located 22 km from Sterlibashevo, 11 km from Bakeyevo. == References == Category:Rural localities in Sterlibashevsky District
title: Nizhniye Karamaly
